p: Other major compounds belonging to monoterpene hydrocarbons were represented in camphene, β-ocimene, β-myrcene, α-terpinene, α-limonene, α-phellandrene and β-pinene and their total percentage was only 2.06 %. On the other hand, farnecene and isocaryophyllene were identified in a total percentage of 2 %, these belong to the hydrocarbon sesquiterpenoid group of essential oils. Oxygenated sesquiterpenoid was found only as nerolidol (0.17 %). Other compounds that are not terpenoid were identified such as 3-octanol (4.38 %) and 3-octanone (1.42 %).
